<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="355" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1271,1944]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,372,1271,1296]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Generic diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body small, form slender. Fastigium verticis stout, conical, its apex obtusely rounded, dorsal surface with 
<number box="[305,319,1308,1332]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1.0">1</number>
median sulcus. Eyes ovoid, protruding forwards. Maxillary palpi comparatively shorter, apical segment nearly as long as subapical one, apices slightly inflated. Pronotum short, humeral sinus distinct. Pro- and mesotibiae with comparatively shorter spines on ventral surface; protibial tympana opened on both sides. Genicular lobes of postfemora with apices obtusely rounded; apices of posttibiae with 
<number box="[999,1013,1416,1440]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of dorsal apical spurs and 
<number box="[1361,1375,1416,1440]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of ventral apical spurs. Tegmina longer, obviously surpassing apices of postfemora; hind wings slightly longer than tegmina. Male tenth abdominal tergite normal, without any process; cerci variable. Ovipositor nearly straight, dorsal and ventral margins smooth, apices of ventral vavulae hook-shaped. Fastigium verticis black; pronotal disc with 
<number box="[210,224,1560,1584]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1.0">1</number>
longitudinal yellowish brown stripe along the midline, anterior margin of pronotum with 
<number box="[1266,1280,1560,1584]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of black brown spots, and metazona with 
<number box="[519,533,1596,1620]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of black brown spots or not.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="355" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1271,1944]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1631,1656]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[683,822,1632,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Alloteratura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[683,822,1632,1656]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Alloteratura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[845,1011,1632,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Meconemopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[845,1011,1632,1655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Meconemopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in: tegmina comparatively longer, obviously surpassing apices of postfemora; dorsal surface of fastigium verticis black brown, pronotal disc with 
<number box="[1392,1406,1668,1692]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1.0">1</number>
or 
<number box="[151,165,1704,1728]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of black brown spots; genicular lobes of postfemora with apices obtusely rounded. The genus may be confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov, 1993" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1993" box="[316,584,1740,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Xizicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[316,397,1741,1764]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Xizicus</emphasis>
Gorochov, 
<number box="[528,584,1740,1764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Redtenbacher, 1891" authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1891" box="[640,1010,1740,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Xiphidiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,780,1740,1764]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Xiphidiopsis</emphasis>
Redtenbacher, 
<number box="[954,1010,1740,1764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1891.0">1891</number>
</taxonomicName>
but the former is without any process on male tenth abdominal tergite and pronotum has 
<number box="[721,735,1776,1800]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1.0">1</number>
or 
<number box="[773,787,1776,1800]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of black brown spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1271,1944]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1812,1837]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Species included.</emphasis>
The new genus includes 
<number box="[686,700,1812,1836]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="3.0">3</number>
known species from South 
<collectingCountry box="[1012,1079,1812,1837]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1244,1813,1837]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bey-Bienko, 1971" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Xiphidiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinotata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Xiphidiopsis quadrinotata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko" box="[319,541,1847,1872]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" refString="Bey-Bienko, G. Ya. (1971) The revision of the bush crickets of the genus Xiphidiopsis Redt. (Orthoptera, Tettigonioidea). Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 50: 827 - 848. [in Russian; English translation: A revision of the bush-crickets of the genus Xiphidiopsis Redt. (Orthoptera, Tettigonioidea). Entomological Review, 50, 472 - 483.]" type="journal article" year="1971">
Bey-Bienko, 
<number box="[483,541,1848,1872]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Jiao &amp; Shi, 2013" authorityName="Jiao &amp; Shi" authorityYear="2013" box="[567,1186,1847,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Xizicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xizangensis" subGenus="Axizicus">
<emphasis box="[567,648,1848,1871]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Xizicus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[679,772,1848,1871]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Axizicus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[803,932,1848,1871]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">xizangensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jiao" box="[954,1186,1847,1872]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" refString="Jiao, J., Shi, F. M. &amp; Gao, J. G. (2013) Two new species of the genus Xizicus, 1993 (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Meconematinae) from Xizang, China. Zootaxa, 3694 (3), 296 - 300. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3694.3.10" type="journal article" year="2013">
Jiao &amp; Shi, 
<number box="[1130,1186,1848,1872]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang, Liu &amp; Li, 2015" authorityName="Wang, Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Meconemopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraquadrinotata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Meconemopsis paraquadrinotata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wang" box="[357,608,1884,1909]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" refString="Wang, H. Q., Liu, X. W. &amp; Li, K. (2015) New taxa of Meconematini (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Meconematinae) from Guangxi, China. Zootaxa, 3941 (4), 509 - 541." type="journal article" year="2015">
Wang, Liu &amp; Li, 
<number box="[549,608,1884,1909]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" value="2015.0">2015</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and one newly described species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1024,1919,1944]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1271,1944]" box="[199,1024,1919,1944]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1919,1944]" pageId="2" pageNumber="355">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named with reference to the black brown spots of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
